com.snamp.connectors

Class WellKnownTypeSystem<E extends EntityTypeInfo>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.snamp.connectors.EntityTypeInfoBuilder<E>
      • com.snamp.connectors.WellKnownTypeSystem<E>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EntityTypeInfoFactory<E>

    public class WellKnownTypeSystem<E extends EntityTypeInfo>
extends EntityTypeInfoBuilder<E>
    Represents a set of well known management entity types.

    You should use this builder for all management entities which values are implicitly compatible with well-known Java types:

    • Int8 - wrapper for Byte class.
    • Int16 - wrapper for Short class.
    • Int32 - wrapper for Integer class.
    • Int64 - wrapper for Long class.
    • String - wrapper for String class.
    • Integer - wrapper for BigInteger class.
    • Decimal - wrapper for BigDecimal class.
    • Boolean - wrapper for Boolean class.
    • Date - wrapper for Date and Calendar classes both.

    For non-scalar data types such as arrays, dictionaries and tables it is recommended to use the following mapping:

    • Tabular and dictionary data should be convertible to Table type. An implementation for this interface is provided by SimpleTable class. Entity data type should implements EntityTabularType interface.
    • Array data should be convertible to Java array and Table type. Attribute data type should inherits from AttributeArrayType class.

    Management entity type system is a set of converters that provides conversion between MIB-specific data types and universal data types. This class provides set of converters between these data types in the form of static public unary methods annotated with EntityTypeInfoBuilder.Converter interface. Typically, each custom SNAMP connector contains its own type system converter, inherited from this class. The following example demonstrates your own type system converter: 

    
 public final class CustomTypeInfoBuilder extends WellKnownTypeSystem<AttributeTypeInfo>{
     public CustomTypeInfoBuilder(){
       super(AttributeTypeInfo.class);
     }

     @Converter
     public static byte[] stringToByteArray(final String str){
         return str.getBytes("UTF-8");
     }

     @Converter
     public static String byteArrayToString(final byte[] b){
         return new String(b, "UTF-8");
     }

     public final AttributeTypeConverter createByteArrayType(){
       return createTypeInfo(getClass(), byte[].class, String.class);
     }
 }

 final CustomTypeInfoBuilder builder = new CustomTypeInfoBuilder();
 final AttributeTypeInfo arrayType = builder.createByteArrayType();
 final String result = arrayType.convertTo(new byte[]{1, 2, 3}, String.class);
